<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 9000 Pro Sleeper After 05/01/1997, and 9800 Model After 07/01/1997 -
        REMOVE AND INSTALL - AIR CONDITIONING AND HEATER CONTROL Cable (9800)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>AIR CONDITIONING AND HEATER CONTROL Cable (9800)</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Batteries expel explosive gases. Keep sparks, flames, burning cigarettes, or other ignition
                        sources away at all times. Always wear safety glasses and a face shield when working near
                        batteries to prevent personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect negative battery cable.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the passenger seat and Blend-Air unit cover. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_17.xml" xrefid="hl1602007">BLEND-AIR UNIT COVER, Remove</hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove floor mat (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602071">Figure 57</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1602071" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602062.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 57. Floor Mat Remove/Install</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f1602063" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602063.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 58. Dash Panel Remove/Install (9800)</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove dash panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602063">Figure 58</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four screws from cab control assembly (
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_HL1602017.xml" xrefid="f1602068">Figure 54</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully slide control assembly out of dash (
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_HL1602017.xml" xrefid="f1602069">Figure 55</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove screw securing HOT-COLD control cable to control assembly (
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_HL1602017.xml" xrefid="f1602070">Figure 56</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove control cable end from HOT-COLD cable lever.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inside Blend-Air unit, remove hold down clamp for HOT-COLD cable. Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602072">Figure 59</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_4.xml" xrefid="f1602001">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inside Blend-Air unit, remove clip that secures HOT-COLD cable to cab Blend-Air door,
                    and disconnect cable from door. Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602072">Figure 59</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_4.xml" xrefid="f1602001">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove HOT-COLD cable from Blend-Air unit and dash, taking note of cable routing and
                    clipping.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1602072" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figG16/G1602018.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="432px"/>
                <caption>Figure 59. Connection of HOT-COLD Cable to Cab Blend-Door Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>In the following step, adjuster end of cable must be located at dash control assembly.</para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Route HOT-COLD cable from dash to Blend-Air unit as previously removed.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify cable works freely and is free of kinks and tight bends.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect cable end to HOT-COLD cable lever on control assembly (
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_HL1602017.xml" xrefid="f1602070">Figure 56</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install screw securing HOT-COLD control cable to control assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide control assembly into dash and secure with four mounting screws (
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_HL1602017.xml" xrefid="f1602068">Figure 54</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inside Blend-Air unit, attach end of HOT-COLD cable to cab Blend-Air door and secure
                    with clip removed previously. Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602072">Figure 59</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inside Blend-Air unit, install hold down clamp for HOT-COLD cable (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602072">Figure 59</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify that the HOT-COLD cable is routed and secured as it originally was.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install dash panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602063">Figure 58</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install floor mat using mounting hardware previously removed (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602071">Figure 57</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the passenger seat and Blend-Air unit cover. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_17.xml" xrefid="hl1602006">BLEND-AIR UNIT COVER, Install</hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Adjust HOT-COLD cable as indicated in the following steps.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After adjustment is completed, connect negative battery cable.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="hl1602020">
            <title>Control Cable - Adjustment</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four screws from cab control assembly (
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_HL1602017.xml" xrefid="f1602068">Figure 54</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully slide control assembly out of dash (
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_HL1602017.xml" xrefid="f1602069">Figure 55</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Set HOT-COLD lever to full HOT position.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn cable adjuster so lever is near end of slot but not touching end of slot.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Move lever to maximum COLD position.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn cable adjuster again so that lever is the same distance from the slot end in both
                    directions.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide control assembly into dash and secure with four mounting screws (
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_HL1602017.xml" xrefid="f1602068">Figure 54</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
